title: Leslie County lineman Blake Asher to walk on for Louisville football
text:
Leslie County High School offensive lineman Blake Asher committed Wednesday night to walk on for the University of Louisville.
The 6-4, 285-pound Asher, who estimated that he's visited U of L six or seven times and camped there this summer, chose the Cardinals over a scholarship offer from FCS-level Austin Peay.
Blake Asher is hopeful and confident of earning a scholarship down the road at U of L, and he's built a good relationship with offensive line coach Chris Klenakis and recruiting administrator Dave Boller.
"It's just a good place, and I feel like I fit in well there," he said. "All the coaches are great people."
Honored to say I am committed to the University of Louisville! #L1C4 pic.twitter.com/a0Q9ASo7se
